title: Sullinger scores 16 to lead Celtics to 99-85 win over Knicks
text:
Home » News » Sports » NBA » Sullinger scores 16 to… Sullinger scores 16 to lead Celtics to 99-85 win over Knicks By GETHIN COOLBAUGH October 22, 2015 10:11 pm Boston Celtics guard Marcus Smart (36) drives past New York Knicks forward Kristaps Porzingis (6) and New York Knicks center Robin Lopez, left, during the first half of a preseason NBA basketball game in Boston, Thursday, Oct. 22, 2015. (AP Photo/Charles Krupa) 
BOSTON (AP) — Jared Sullinger scored 16 points and grabbed eight rebounds to help lead the Boston Celtics to a 99-85 preseason victory over the New York Knicks on Thursday night. 
Celtics: Sullinger was 6 of 10 and had six assists in 19 minutes. … Tyler Zeller finished with 15 points and Jae Crowder added 13. … David Lee had seven points and eight boards. 
Knicks: Carmelo Anthony scored eight points on 4-of-18 shooting in 31 minutes. … Jose Calderon tallied 17 points and eight rebounds. … Derrick Williams added 14 points. 
Star watch: Anthony struggled, missing six of his first seven shots. He was held scoreless for over 20 minutes until a pair of baskets late in the first half. 
Midseason form: Boston’s Marcus Smart dished out nine assists, tying his personal best. 
Up next: New York opens the regular season at Milwaukee on Wednesday. Boston wraps up its preseason schedule against Philadelphia on Friday. Topics:
